<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF336A8CF7ED9C241771B7AE" pageId="200" pageNumber="962" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF336A8CF7ED9C241771B7AE" blockId="200.[2064,2658,2567,2990]" lastBlockId="200.[1453,2661,2998,3464]" pageId="200" pageNumber="962">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF336A8CF73E9C241717B1A8" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[2242,2327,2685,2714]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="962" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF336A8CF6BB9C2417D9B1A8" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[2375,2521,2685,2714]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="962" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">montivagus</taxonomicName>
species group. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF336A8CF77D9CFC1756B1F0" box="[2177,2390,2725,2754]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="962" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="federatus">Myotis federatus</taxonomicName>
has been considered a subspecies, a distinct species, and synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF336A8CF6E99CA917D7B023" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[2325,2519,2800,2833]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">M. montivagus</taxonomicName>
, however, based on morphological and morphometric differences, M. federatus was separated from 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF336A8CF7909D3E173AB0BA" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[2156,2362,2919,2952]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">M. montivagus</taxonomicName>
in 2013. Although M. federatus has not been included in any published phylogenetic study, two samples from 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF336A8CF79B9DEF16E2B0E5" box="[2151,2274,2998,3031]" country="Malaysia" name="Selangor" pageId="200" pageNumber="962">Selangor</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF336A8CF70A9DEF176DB0E5" box="[2294,2413,2998,3031]" name="Malaysia" pageId="200" pageNumber="962">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, were sequenced with 5% divergence, suggesting existence of cryptic species. Uncertainty about relationships of M. federatus to other taxa of the 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF336A8CF7DD9A5016B4B714" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[2081,2228,3081,3110]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="962" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">montivagus</taxonomicName>
species group (e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF336A8CF62D9A501BCFB77F" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="962" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="indochinensis">indochinensis</taxonomicName>
, borneoensis, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF336A8CF93F9A751955B77F" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1731,1877,3116,3149]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="962" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">montivagus</taxonomicName>
) needs to be clarified with morphological and genetic comparison acrossits distribution. Species formerly grouped under the name 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF336A8CF6049A0A180DB7AE" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="200" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">M. montivagus</taxonomicName>
might form a natural grouping ofrelated species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF336A8CFA529AFB19B2B626" pageId="200" pageNumber="962" type="distribution">
<caption id="90EB6676FF336A8CFA529AFB19B2B626" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398898" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398898/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="200" pageNumber="962" targetBox="[1450,2041,2575,2990]" targetPageId="200">
