<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF326A8DFF8595B21D02BF00" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" type="activity">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF326A8DFF8595B21D02BF00" blockId="201.[121,1329,293,1435]" pageId="201" pageNumber="963">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF326A8DFF8595B21F69BF3E" bold="true" box="[121,361,1003,1036]" pageId="201" pageNumber="963">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The Malaysian Whiskered 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF326A8DFD0695B51D53BF3F" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[762,851,1004,1037]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
is nocturnal. One specimen was caught at the Batu Caves, near 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF326A8DFDCC924B1CFEBF00" box="[560,766,1041,1075]" country="Malaysia" name="Kuala Lumpur" pageId="201" pageNumber="963">Kuala Lumpur</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF326A8DFF8792631A27BF69" box="[123,1063,1082,1116]" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" type="biology_ecology">
